    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Clean, proportional fix. Deterministic transport injection replaces a racy server-shutdown approach. `RoundTripperFunc` follows the stdlib `http.HandlerFunc` adapter pattern. Good test density.\n\nSeverity: 0 P0-P1, 1 P3, 3 Nit, 1 Note.\n\n> \"The old test played a timing game with a closing server and lost.\" *-- Hisoka*\n\n\n---\n\n`codersdk/workspaces_test.go:1`\n\n**P3** [CRF-2] The implementation plan in the PR description describes a code state that does not exist at the base SHA. It claims \"ENG-2840 added a small function adapter\" and instructs to \"Remove the local `transportErrorFunc` helper,\" but neither a function adapter nor `transportErrorFunc` exists at the base. The base uses `httptest.NewServer` + `srv.Close()`. The plan describes \"moving\" a helper; the diff replaces a server-closure strategy with an injected RoundTripper. The implementation is correct, but the plan contains unverified claims about the starting state. *(Mafu-san)*\n\n> \ud83e\udd16\n\n> \ud83e\udd16 This review was automatically generated with Coder Agents.\n",
